title: London/Westminster
name: Whitehall
content: This street runs between Parliament Square and [[London/Leicester Square|Trafalgar Square]], and is the site of several British government buildings. Horseguards Parade, and the heavily guarded entrance to ''Downing Street'' (see below) are on the west side. Banqueting House is on the east side. In the centre of the street sits the Cenotaph, a war memorial erected following the World War I, which is the centre of the annual Remembrance Day ceremony on 11 November.
